feedback: I had to make multiple attempts to pass the test page (and in the end ticked the radio buttons semi-randomly). I wonder if you have sat a few people in front of you and watched them attempt the test and seen the results. The instructions (and test questions) may not be as clear to a random person as they are to the person that wrote them. E.g. in the instructions I think there may be an inconsistency at one point between the concept of collecting crystals and points.  I didnt understand why Im allowed to have the machine process a single new crystal multiple times (I assumed that wouldnt be allowed) and therefore didnt see the benefit in wasting clicks on additional new crystals as there was no evidence any would offer more than 150 points.
